## Context

- nod2-variant-functional-impact: Completed comprehensive analysis of the NOD2 3-class classifier (GOF/neutral/LOF)
- **Critical finding:** Model has collapsed to a neutral classifier due to extreme class imbalance (5 GOF / 301 neutral / 5 LOF)
  - LOF recall=0.0, GOF LOO accuracy=1/5, LOF LOO accuracy=0/5
  - Macro AUC=0.779 is misleading (inflated by neutral class)
- **Feature ablation:** AlphaMissense (importance #1, 0.21) is counterproductive — AUC=0.474 alone, removing it improves AUC to 0.820. Domain features alone achieve AUC=0.881, GOF recall=0.80, LOF recall=1.00. Predictor scores collectively hurt 3-class performance.
- **Girdin validation:** Partially validated. 2/5 LOF near girdin interface (L1007fs, G908R), 3/5 far away. Mann-Whitney p=0.79 (NS). Feature confounded with LRR domain membership. Promising lead, not confirmed.
- **VUS confidence:** 440 high-conf are 83% neutral predictions. 64/125 GOF predictions outside NACHT/WH (suspect). 19 high-conf GOF in LRR are likely false positives. Top credible GOF candidate: p.Arg334Pro (same residue as validated Blau GOF).
- Created tasks: 896 (data_curator: augment training set), 897 (developer: 2-stage model), plus 2 research_director review tasks
- Next: await augmented training set (Task 896) before re-running analysis. Current VUS predictions should be labeled exploratory only.
